name: iden·​ti·​ty
description:
iden·​ti·​ty | \ ī-ˈden-tə-tē : Sameness in all that constitutes the objective reality of a thing

What is anonymous identity? This piece explores the concept of identity and anonymity through portraits of "Satoshi Nakamoto" created by generative adversarial networks, where portraits of two different algorithmic characters interpolate into each other by creating sameness
